label: University of Pennsylvania LJS 416: Regulations for mills and bakeries
attribution: Provided by the University of Pennsylvania Libraries
description:
Summary: Official copies of regulations pertaining to mills and bakeries in Rouen from the 14th century up to 1518. The copies were made at the request of Pierre Tassel, overseer of the Rouen mills (fermier des moulins de la dit ville de Rouen), under the supervision of Louis (Loys) Cruchon, a member of the Rouen parliament, who signed the manuscript repeatedly (f. 9v, 13v, 16r).
        Language: Middle French
        Support: parchment
        Extent: 
        Collation: Parchment, i + 28 + i; 1-2⁸ 3⁶ 4⁴; [1-28], modern foliation in pencil, lower right recto.
        Layout: Written in 18 long lines; frame-ruled in red ink.
        Script: Written in a semi-batârde script, with contemporary signatures at the end of each section except the last (f. 9v, 13v, 16r), possibly in two hands (f. 1r-16r, 17r-26r).
        Decoration: 4-line initial in red (f. 17r); 3-line calligraphic initial (f. 14r); 2-line initial with grotesque face in profile (f. 22r); one rubric in red (f. 10v); line-fillers in red and blue; initials touched with yellow wash.
        Binding: Contemporary morocco, blind-stamped, lacking spine and clasps.
        Origin: Written in Rouen, between August (f. 9v) and October (f. 16r) 1518, for Pierre Tassel (f. 9v, 13v, 16r).
        Cite as:	
        UPenn LJS 416
        For catalog record, see Permanent Link: 5001566 http://hdl.library.upenn.edu/1017/d/medren/5001566
  For TEI description and digital images, see: http://openn.library.upenn.edu/Data/LJSchoenbergManuscripts/html/ljs416.html
